definitions.definition: To expel air as a reflex induced by an irritation in the nose .
examples: To avoid passing on your illness, you should sneeze into your sleeve.

definitions.definition: To expel air as if the nose were irritated.
To expel or displace (air, snot , etc) from the nose or mouth by the process above.

main_definition: ( intransitive , medicine ) To expel air as a reflex induced by an irritation in the nose .
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive ) To expel air as if the nose were irritated.
( transitive ) To expel or displace (air, snot , etc) from the nose or mouth by the process above.
